1. C++ is a middle-level programming language
2. Developed by Bjarne Stroustrup (B-yar-ne Strov-stroop) in 1979 at Bell Labs.

Why Learn C++?
There are 1000 reasons to learn C++ but I have listed few according to my prefference
1. Close to hardware, control on memory management, better performance and robust software development.
2. OOPS
3. Professionally rewarding.
4. Most used language in application and system programming.
5. Teaches you difference between compiler and loader, different data types, storage classes, variable types and thier scopes etc.

Applications of C++
1. Application Software Development
2. Programming Languages Development
3. Computation Programming
4. Games Development
5. Embedded System and so on...
